events.name: Toronto Maple Leafs at Buffalo Sabres

headlines.description: — Defenseman Mattias Samuelsson scored twice and the Buffalo Sabres snapped a five-game skid against the rival Toronto Maple Leafs with a 5-3 victory Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Samuelsson scores twice and Tuch adds short-handed goal in Sabres' 5-3 win over Maple Leafs

headlines.shortLinkText: Ovechkin scores 899th goal as Capitals beat Blue Jackets 5-1 for 6th win in 7 games
